item.title: About Us
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
Check out our privacy policy here

After we realized this problem and discussed it deeply about it, we have decided to provide a platform to create a better connection between employers and employees, which stands for people who seek jobs and people who are hiring for their own good, in order to reduce more side effects caused by unemployment in Singapore.

 

Founded in Singapore in 2021, JOB4U now has a team of 100 talented individuals, giving us a strong local presence in every country in which we operate.

 

With our understanding and insights on each market, as well our passion for technology, we provide jobseekers the best opportunities and deliver exceptional value to employers.

 

We are committed to continuously improving the value we provide to jobseekers and employers. To deliver on this, we continue to evolve our product and service offerings to better facilitate the matching of jobseekers to employers.

item.title: Terms and privacy policy
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
Your privacy is important to JOB4U.com. Please read this Privacy Notice carefully as it forms part of the Terms of Use which govern the use of the JOB4U.com Services and the JOB4U.com Websites.
This Privacy Notice explains-:
  1. The type of personal information about you which is processed by Job4u.com when you use the JOB4U.com Services and/or the JOB4U.com
  2. How JOB4U.com processes the personal information about you when you use the Job4u.com Services and the JOB4U.com Websites;
  3. The purposes for which JOB4U.com collects and processes your personal information;
  4. Your right to access and correct your personal information. 
  5. Whether it is obligatory or voluntarily for you to supply the personal information and the consequences of failing to provide your personal information when it is obligatory; and
  6. How Job4u.com safeguards the confidentiality and security of your personal information.
    Any changes will be notified to you via the e-mail address provided by you on registration or via a suitable announcement on the JOB4U.com Websites. If we make any material changes we will notify you by email (sent to the e-mail address specified in your account) or by means of a notice on this Site prior to the change becoming effective. The changes will apply to the use of the JOB4U.com Services and the JOB4U.com Websites after JOB4U.com have given you notice. If you do not wish to accept the new Terms you should not continue to use the JOB4U.com Services and/or the JOB4U.com Websites. If you continue to use the JOB4U.com Services and/or the JOB4U.com Websites after the date on which the changes comes into effect, your use of the JOB4U.com Services and/or the JOB4U.com Websites indicates your agreement to be bound by the new Terms.
In this Privacy Notice:-
“JOB4U.com Profile” means the profile created by users of the websites that may include personal information, resume and photo.
“personal information” is data that can be used to identify an individual.
“processing” includes but is not limited to collecting, holding, storing, recording, organizing, adapting, using, disclosing, correcting, destructing.
    1. When you register for the services
      1. Each time when you register with JBO4U.com for any of the services, you will be asked to provide certain personal information about yourself in order to create a JOB4U.com account.
      2. The personal information collected during the registration process includes but is not limited to your email address, name, nationality,  country of residence.
      3. Whenever the personal information requested by JOB4U.com is marked as “Required Field”, you must provide and agree to the processing of this personal information. If you do not agree to provide this personal information and/or not agree to us processing it in the manner set out in this Privacy Notice, then JOB4U.com will be unable to provide the relevant services to you and your application for such services will be rejected.
        COLLECTION OF PERSONAL INFORMATIONFrom your use of the website:
      1. We collect personal information directly from you when you choose to engage any of the websites. The following are examples of personal information JOB4U.com may collect directly from you:-
        1. Age;
        2. Date of birth;
        3. Telephone number or mobile number;
        4. Your image;
        5. Academic qualifications;
        6. Identification documents given by the school/college/university/institute;
        7. Resume;
        8. Personal interests and preferences;
        9. Working experience;
        10. Other information associated with a resume for job applications
  2. PURPOSES OF COLLECTING AND USE OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
    1. The purposes for which JOB4U.com processes your personal information are as follows:-
      1. To verify your identity;
      2. To assess and/or verify your employability and credit worthiness;
      3. To provide the services which you have requested;
      4. To administer and manage the services provided to you;
      5. To contact you in respect of services;
      6. To facilitate the provision to you of tailored educational offerings and improve your career prospects by supplying your information to our strategic partners;
      7. To improve placement opportunities for you including through using artificial intelligence (“AI”) and data analytics in relation to your personal information to improve the ability of website to better assist you in finding appropriate opportunities and to assist Employers to assess the suitability of candidates for job vacancy for a wide spectrum of jobs and industries; or
      8. or for tailoring specific services to you;
      9. To verify your academic and professional qualification by contacting the school/college/university/institute/ professional qualifying bodies;
      10. To contact the referee and/or the guarantor whom details have been provided by you;
      11. To process your order for the services which you have requested;
      12. To investigate and resolve any of the services, complaints or other enquiries that you submit to JOB4U.com;
      13. To manage staff training and quality assurance;
      14. To monitor and improve the performance of the websites and the services;
      15. To maintain and develop the websites and services;
      16. To gain an understanding of your information and communication needs in order for JOB4U.com to enhance and customize the services;
      17. To conduct research and development and statistical analysis in connection with the services to identify trends and develop new services that reflect your interests;
    2. In addition, JOB4U.com may use your personal information for the following purposes:-
      1. To promote and market to you:
        1. Other JOB4U.com Services; or
        2. Services of third parties which JOB4U.com thinks may be of interest of you;
      2. To send you seasonal greeting messages and/or message informing you of a critical performance error in the JOB4U.com Websites and/or the JOB4U.com Services.
      3. To send you tips, advice and survey information to maximize your career development including but not limited to using the JOB4U.com Services and/or the JOB4U.com Websites.
    3. JOB4U.com will ask for your consent before processing your personal information other than those set out in Clauses 2.1 and 2.3.
  3. CHOICE AND ACCESS OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
    1. You may have different privacy concerns. You can control who you share your personal information with;
      1. You can review and control your subscription to various marketing preferences;
      2. You may view, edit or delete your personal information and preferences at any time.
      3. You may choose not to receive any marketing materials;
      4. You may also subscribe to additional Services by logging into account;
      5. You can delete your account at any time in which event  will remove all access to your account, resume and 
  4. SECURITY OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
    1. JOB4U.com is committed to keeping personal information secure. We has appropriate technical, administrative and physical procedures in place to protect personal information from loss, theft and misuse, as well as against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration and destruction. 
    2. No method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure, however. Therefore, we cannot guarantee its absolute security. If you have any questions about security on our Web site, you can contact us.
